<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFCBFF81A7ADF9E0FEAFDB20" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFCBFF81A7ADF9E0FEB8DA29" blockId="82.[189,382,1550,1577]" box="[189,382,1550,1577]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFCBFF81A7ADF9E0FEB8DA29" bold="true" box="[189,382,1550,1577]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFCBFF81A7ADF9E0FEB8DA29" bold="true" box="[189,382,1550,1577]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Natural history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFCBFF81A7ADF9AEFEAFDB20" blockId="82.[189,1399,1601,1825]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
The cave in which the 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FFCBFF81A6D7F9AEFDE8DA5A" box="[455,558,1601,1627]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected is located in a tropical dry forest, at an altitude of 
<specimenCount id="11EC69EAFFCBFF81A235F9ADFAB1DA5D" box="[1317,1399,1602,1628]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="generic">
<quantity id="C0120F86FFCBFF81A235F9ADFAB4DA5D" box="[1317,1394,1602,1628]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.37" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" unit="m" value="337.0">337 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
The outside forest is warm and dry, with an average temperature of 26.8°C, relative humidity of 77%, and annual precipitation between 1000 and 
<quantity id="C0120F86FFCBFF81A5C7F97FFC88DAAA" box="[727,846,1680,1707]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="1200.0">1200 mm</quantity>
. The 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FFCBFF81A487F97FFC38DAAB" box="[919,1022,1680,1706]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected under a rock in the twilight zone of the cave and, at the time of sampling, the air temperature was 27°C and relative humidity of 80%. 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFCBFF81A682F930FB75DAFB" authority="Armas, Torres-Contreras &amp; Alvarez, 2015" authorityName="Armas, Torres-Contreras &amp; Alvarez" authorityYear="2015" box="[402,1203,1759,1786]" class="Arachnida" family="Phrynidae" genus="Heterophrynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFCBFF81A682F930FD07DAF8" box="[402,705,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Heterophrynus caribensis</emphasis>
Armas, Torres-Contreras &amp; Alvarez, 2015
</taxonomicName>
was collected in the same cave.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFCBFF81A7ADF8A2FCACDBE9" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
